{"word":"μαίσων","slug":"μαίσων","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<entryFree id=\"n64571\" key=\"mai/swn\" type=\"main\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"entryFree\"> <orth extent=\"full\" lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"orth\">μαίσων</orth>, <itype lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"itype\">ωνος</itype>, <gen lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"gen\">ὁ</gen>, <sense id=\"n64571.0\" n=\"A\" level=\"1\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"sense\"> <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">native cook</tr_>, at Athens, <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0008.tlg001.perseus-grc1:14:659a\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Ath.\">Ath.</a></author> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">14.659a</biblScope> </bibl>; derived from <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">μασᾶσθαι</foreign> by Chrysipp.ibid., but acc. to Ar.Byz.ibid. it means <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">comic mask of a cook, sailor</tr_>, etc., named after an actor so called:—hence <orth extent=\"full\" lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"orth\">μαισωνικὰ</orth> <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">σκώμματα</foreign>, ib.b.</sense> </entryFree>"}]}